# Installation and Setup

## Installation Guidelines
- never forget to work with a python virtual environment
- make sure to install all dependencies as per the [pyproject.toml](mdc:pyproject.toml) and [requirements.txt](mdc:requirements.txt)
- be aware that you will clone kodosumi from Github and checkout the dev branch
- make sure to exclude the kodosumi folder as part of the .gitignore setup
- after a full installation run first all tests first with pytest to see if everything works

## Setup of the Environment
- make sure that the user setups the API Keys in the .ENV file before running the code
- make sure to run the Ray Head in the background as described in the [README.md](mdc:README.md)
- make sure to run the Kodosumi Spooler in the background as desribed in the [README.md](mdc:README.md)
- make sure to deploy the [config.yaml](mdc:config.yaml) to with serve as described in the [README.md](mdc:README.md)
- make sure to run the Kodosumi servie as described in the [README.md](mdc:README.md)